name: FGameplayCueParameters
doc: Metadata about a gameplay cue execution

NormalizedMagnitude: Magnitude of source gameplay effect, normalzed from 0-1. Use this for "how strong is the gameplay effect" (0=min, 1=,max)
RawMagnitude: Raw final magnitude of source gameplay effect. Use this is you need to display numbers or for other informational purposes.
EffectContext: Effect context, contains information about hit result, etc
MatchedTagName: The tag name that matched this specific gameplay cue handler
OriginalTag: The original tag of the gameplay cue
AggregatedSourceTags: The aggregated source tags taken from the effect spec
AggregatedTargetTags: The aggregated target tags taken from the effect spec
Normal: Normal of impact that caused cue
Instigator: Instigator actor, the actor that owns the ability system component
EffectCauser: The physical actor that actually did the damage, can be a weapon or projectile
SourceObject: Object this effect was created from, can be an actor or static object. Useful to bind an effect to a gameplay object
PhysicalMaterial: PhysMat of the hit, if there was a hit.
GameplayEffectLevel: If originating from a GameplayEffect, the level of that GameplayEffect
AbilityLevel: If originating from an ability, this will be the level of that ability
TargetAttachComponent: Could be used to say "attach FX to this component always"
bReplicateLocationWhenUsingMinimalRepPro: If we're using a minimal replication proxy, should we replicate location for this cue
